				<p><p>I think you could use <em>bearing</em> (or <em>azimuth</em> or <em>right ascension</em>) and <em>mark</em> (or <em>altitude</em> or <em>declination</em>). For example 0 mark 0 is straight ahead and on the horizon. 30 mark 30 is 30 degrees to the right and 30 degrees above the horizon. -90 mark -90 would be 90 degrees to the left and then face down into the ground.  These could be relative to your current position and orientation or relative to some reference such as true north or magnetic north and the horizon. </p>

