<li>The terminology is rich. There are unambiguous terms for location (left right anterior posterior dorsal ventral), the cross section planes (sagital transverse coronal), and relative positioning on the body (proximal distal).</li>
<li>The terminology is shared. Roboticists doing medical, walking, and manipulation use these terms and the fact that biologists and medical scientists can instantly understand you creates opportunities for scientific cross-pollination. </li>
